If STASH_HOME is set as an environment variable and not in setenv.sh, and Stash is started up manually and the {{-Dstash.home=$STASH_HOME}} JVM  option isn't passed in, Catalina throws an error on startup and shutdown of stash

{code}
WARNING: Problem with directory [/<stash_installation_directory>/${stash.home}/lib], exists: [false], isDirectory: [false], canRead: [false]
{code}

As the system property isn't set, the replacement isn't happening and it is looking for a literal {{$\{stash.home\}/lib}} directory in the file system.

When upgrading from Stash 2.8.3 to Stash 2.10.0, a bug that was [supposedly fixed|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/STASH-3096] is recurring. When shutting down Stash, the following warnings are encountered:

{code}
Dec 23, 2013 3:48:22 PM org.apache.catalina.startup.ClassLoaderFactory validateFile
WARNING: Problem with directory [/home/stash/${stash.home}/lib], exists: [false], isDirectory: [false], canRead: [false]
